%N A397608 Decimal expansion of the volume of a canonical (dual-uniform) hexagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397608 The hexagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the hexagonal antiprism.
%H A397608 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397608/b397608.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A397608 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HexagonalTrapezohedron.html">Hexagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397608 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Hexagonal_antitegum">Hexagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397608 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397608 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexagonal_trapezohedron">Hexagonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397608 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A397608 Equals sqrt(2*(97 + 56*sqrt(3))) = sqrt(2*(97 + 56*A002194)).
%F A397608 Equals the largest root of x^4 - 388*x^2 + 4.
%e A397608 19.697453907744377734400957368291452117851493050265...
%t A397608 First[RealDigits[Sqrt[2*(97 + 56*Sqrt[3])], 10, 100]]
%t A397608 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397608 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 6}, "Volume"], 10, 100]]
